I need ability to build Lighthouse and stone at the island where I can do notes.

I am writing this after beating first (and the hardest - Lusca the Great) boss in game. This game is a huge disappointment.

So what happens? Well, I killed the boss.

Did I enjoy the fight? Hell nope..
Do I want to fight another bosses? Nope, thanks.
Do I want to finish game after this crap? Not really.
Do I want a refund? Would be nice, but I played too long, preparing for bosses, mindlessly collecting resources and building raft.. too long.

And more about boss fight itself:

Some flickering model under the buoy, constantly changing direction, without clear attack pattern or anything. It just pull me from raft as soon as I get climbed on it. In-between I was shooting from speargun (top game weapon). Once I used bandage. Then boss glitches, it had 0 hp on screen while I was shooting and shooting.

During the fight storm begin. No devs had thought to make boss fight easier by preventing game freaking weather change. Oh I hate weather so much, it disrupt all my activities constantly with storm or huge waves.. it is so annoying to loose time before I can finally enjoy a bit of diving and scavenging for resources with a good sunny weather. Did I say sunny? Game has night, to make everything dark and annoy you even more... 

I was disrupted, sorry.. 

Storm begun and it become impossible to see the boss from the surface, so I went into a water, pretty sure I will be dead in no time. But no I wasn't instantly killed or anything. So I was just shooting and shooting.

Somehow it died and body immediately disappear, without letting me to recover ammo, I only saw how all arrows quickly drown. I had 48 and my hunting skill 6/7, means I should be doing quite some damage. Did I miss a lot? Not really, the boss was like hedgehog in arrows.

And after boss fight I had to sail back to my island to restock. And you know what happen? I just get lost, good thing I didn't save yet, so I can load game and enjoy boss fight again... ><

---

Everything I am doing in this game feels clunky:
- clunky combat, huge hit boxes, huge reach of enemy hits, either on the ground or under the water;
- clunky boss fights (read above);
- clunky craft, UI doesn't remember what I just crafted, after crafting 1 item I need to find it again in a huge list with many tabs;
- clunky exploration with clunky weather and clunky dangerous fishes/snakes which can hide or swim directly to you, await for you in an unexpected room of drown ship to poison you;
- clunky navigation, where game engine doesn't render game objects (e.g. a huge ship) or lights on my base, rendering either surrounding useless for navigation, all islands looks nearly the same, little, boring, with few ships around each..
- clunky survival, eat coconut 3 times and you are dead, can't even skip the night, because wake up time is freaking random;
- clunky raft building, when everything is in red color, refusing to build;
- clunky base building, you can't have a nice base, something require ugly ground;
- clunky inventory system, I doubt a worse system exists;
- clunky island generation, the stone/clay deposit may spawn inside the ship, the inpenetrateable bushes may cover valuable resource spawn;
- clunky enemies, they are buggy, flew, getting throwing into a water, run in circles, I bet any beginner gamedev would write a better AI than devs of this game did..
- clunky UI, you can't even say for sure what level your skill..

And more:

- no vitals on screen, to check HP you need to hold some button and switch to a proper tab out of 3;
- lots of bugs;
- building doesn't return resources, they don't even have sound associated, nor show their health, simply disappear after hitting few times with an axe;
- fish can swim on island;
- boar can swim on the bottom of the sea;
- shark can go through stone and sand on a shallow water;

I stop here. DO NOT buy this game. DO NOT support devs, who out of sudden release 1.0 without polishing their game first.

Another early access shame ventured to nowhere.. ><
